7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Longshot AI and Wordtune share a solid foundation of core features including Short Form, Tone Control. Where Longshot AI pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Long Form and Seo Tools and Templates and Plagiarism Check and Team Collaboration, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Wordtune uniquely offers Multilingual and Browser Extension, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Longshot AI holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Wordtune scores 7/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Wordtune comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Longshot AI begins at $19/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Longshot AI's free tier and Wordtune's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
