b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Longshot AI is best suited for fact checked content, SEO articles, blog posts, research heavy writing, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Wordtune, meanwhile, shines for rewriting, tone adjustment, non native English speakers, academic writing, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2021, Longshot AI describes itself as \"AI writing tool with built-in fact-checking and citations.\" Wordtune, established in 2018, positions itself as \"AI rewriting tool that helps you say exactly what you mean.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Wordtune** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Longshot AI is a poor choice — far from it. Longshot AI excels in its own right, particularly for fact checked content and SEO articles.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class sentence rewriting and rephrasing, go with Wordtune. If unique fact-checking and citation features matters more to you, Longshot AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
